        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(kilocode): normalize string stop param to array in stream wrapper",
        "body": "The Kilo.ai Gateway rejects chat completion requests when `stop` is a plain string instead of a JSON array. This causes 400 errors on cron tasks and nested subagent runs using `deepseek-v4-flash` via the `kilo` provider.\n\nFixes #86074\n\n## Summary\n\nNormalize `payload.stop` from `string` to `[string]` inside the Kilocode provider-owned `createKilocodeWrapper` stream helper. Array and absent `stop` values pass through unchanged.\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\nBehavior addressed: Kilo provider 400 rejection on string stop param\nReal environment tested: macOS 15.5, Node 24.2.0, local OpenClaw dev checkout\nExact steps or command run after this patch: pnpm test src/agents/pi-embedded-runner/proxy-stream-wrappers.test.ts && pnpm check:changed\nEvidence after fix: terminal output from running the proxy stream wrapper tests after the patch:\n```\n$ pnpm test src/agents/pi-embedded-runner/proxy-stream-wrappers.test.ts\n ✓ |unit-fast| src/agents/pi-embedded-runner/proxy-stream-wrappers.test.ts (11 tests) 3ms\n Test Files  1 passed (1)\n      Tests  11 passed (11)\n\n$ pnpm check:changed\nFound 0 warnings and 0 errors.\nImport cycle check: 0 runtime value cycle(s).\n```\nTwo new test cases verify the normalization:\n1. `normalises string stop to array` - sends `stop: \"END\"`, asserts patched payload has `stop: [\"END\"]`\n2. `leaves array stop unchanged` - sends `stop: [\"END\", \"STOP\"]`, asserts array passes through untouched\n\nObserved result after fix: string stop values are wrapped in an array before reaching the Kilo API; array values pass through unchanged\nWhat was not tested: live Kilo.ai endpoint (no API key available locally)\n",
        "branch": "fix/kilo-stop-string-to-array",
